{"cursor":"13518","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\nThe 'International Communist League (Fourth Internationalist)', earlier known as\nthe 'international Spartacist tendency' is a Trotskyist international. Its\nlargest constituent party is the Spartacist League (US). There are smaller\nsections of the ICL (FI) in Mexico, Canada, France, Germany, Ireland, Italy,\nJapan, South Africa, Australia, Greece, Poland and the United Kingdom.\n\nThe group originated within the \"Revolutionary Tendency\" of the Socialist\nWorkers Party and, upon its expulsion from the SWP, it named itself \"Spartacist\"\nin 1964 in homage to the original Spartacist League in World War I Germany co-\nled by Rosa Luxemburg and Karl Liebknecht.\n","linknr":304,"url":"International_Spartacist_Tendency","recorded":1362675199,"links":15,"instances":["swp","united_states","us","united_states","sweden","sri_lanka","united_states"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Trotskyist political internationals","Organizations established in 1974"],"headings":["Publications","Positions","History","Affiliates","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/de/Logo_of_the_Fourth_International.svg/75px-Logo_of_the_Fourth_International.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["spartacist_league","us"],["socialist_workers_party","us"],["democratic_party","united_states"],["green_party","united_states"],["socialist_workers_party","united_states"],["revolutionary_tendency","swp"],["socialist_workers_party","united_states"],["workers_league","us"],["revolutionary_workers_party","sri_lanka"],["spartacist_league","us"],["spartacist_league","sweden"]],"members":["re